“土必为你的缘故受咒诅
"Cursed be the ground for our sake.

192
00:32:08,176 --> 00:32:13,515
“地必给你长出荆棘和蒺藜
"Both thorns and thistles it shall bring forth for us.

193
00:32:15,767 --> 00:32:19,646
“因为你本生于土，土归土
"For out of the ground, we were taken. For the dust, we are.

194
00:32:22,023 --> 00:32:24,693
“尘归尘”
"And to the dust, we shall return."

195
00:32:53,430 --> 00:32:54,931
住手！
Stop!

196
00:32:57,434 --> 00:32:58,768
拜托
Please.

197
00:33:10,071 --> 00:33:11,573
瑞德吉！
Redridge!

198
00:33:12,282 --> 00:33:13,575
瑞德吉
Redridge.

199
00:33:27,714 --> 00:33:29,424
你是谁？
And who are you?

200
00:33:30,467 --> 00:33:31,676
无名之辈
Nobody.

201
00:33:33,178 --> 00:33:35,430
我不相信
I doubt that.

202
00:33:35,513 --> 00:33:39,476
你在我酒吧里杀的人，他们才是无名之辈
The men you killed in my bar, now, they were nobody.

203
00:33:40,769 --> 00:33:43,146
- 但你却是个大人物- 他的手没抖
- But you, now.- He ain't got the shakes.

204
00:33:43,230 --> 00:33:45,690
- 他不是食人族- 很好
- He ain't one of them.- Good.

205
00:33:46,483 --> 00:33:50,278
这是一个文明的地方，我们不吃人类
This is a civilized town.We don't eat humans.

206
00:33:51,655 --> 00:33:55,283
大灾难之前的人我们见的不多，现在不是了
We don't see too many people from before. Not anymore.

207
00:33:57,327 --> 00:33:59,996
- 你读书吗？- 每天
- Do you read?- Every day.

208
00:34:00,330 --> 00:34:03,625
很好，对你好，我也是
All right. Well, good for you. Me, too.

209
00:34:04,584 --> 00:34:05,919
很滑稽
You know, it's funny.

210
00:34:06,002 --> 00:34:10,799
像你我这样老的人，我们是未来
As old as we are, people like you and me, we're the future.

211
00:34:11,675 --> 00:34:12,968
你想从我这得到什么？
What do you want with me?

212
00:34:13,969 --> 00:34:15,470
直奔主题！
Straight to the point!

213
00:34:16,846 --> 00:34:18,765
我喜欢！
I like that!

214
00:34:18,848 --> 00:34:20,267
我喜欢！

215
00:34:24,896 --> 00:34:26,690
你不仅仅受过教育
You're not just educated.

216
00:34:28,191 --> 00:34:30,652
我没见过像你这样身手不凡的
I never saw anyone handle themselves the way you did.

217
00:34:30,735 --> 00:34:35,407
我不知道你从哪里学到的
但我肯定我能用上你
I don't know where you learned it,but I sure as hell could use it.

218
00:34:35,490 --> 00:34:39,411
这个小地方，只是一个开始
This little town, just the beginning.

219
00:34:39,494 --> 00:34:41,579
我准备扩建它
I'm about to expand.

220
00:34:41,663 --> 00:34:43,999
我需要高手的帮助，我需要像你这样的人
I need expert help. I
could use someone like you.

221
00:34:44,583 --> 00:34:47,544
谢谢，但我不感兴趣
Thank you, but I'm really not interested.

222
00:34:48,211 --> 00:34:50,964
为我工作的人，生活得比任何行者想像的都好
Well, the people who work for me live better than any walker ever dreamed.

223
00:34:51,047 --> 00:34:53,675
问问瑞德吉，问问这些年轻人，谁都行
Ask Redridge here. Ask the boys, anyone.

224
00:34:54,551 --> 00:34:56,803
真正的床，热乎的饭菜，女人
Real beds, hot food, women.

225
00:34:59,889 --> 00:35:01,516
干净的水
Clean water.

226
00:35:02,475 --> 00:35:04,728
你可能会过得更糟，朋友
You could do a lot worse, my friend.

227
00:35:06,229 --> 00:35:07,606
谢谢
Thank you,

228
00:35:09,399 --> 00:35:11,776
但我需要去一个地方
but I got somewhere I need to be.

229
00:35:11,860 --> 00:35:13,153
哪里？
Where?

230
00:35:14,279 --> 00:35:15,447
西边
West.

231
00:35:15,989 --> 00:35:17,782
西边什么都没有
There is nothing west.

232
00:35:17,866 --> 00:35:19,826
有人告诉我不是这样
I've been told different.

233
00:35:19,909 --> 00:35:21,202
谁？
By who?

234
00:35:26,708 --> 00:35:28,043
告诉你
Tell you what.

235
00:35:28,126 --> 00:35:33,048
在这儿过夜，感受一下当地的款待，看看你喜不喜欢
Stay the night. Try a little localhospitality, see how you like it.

236
00:35:33,757 --> 00:35:35,550
我们早上再聊
We'll talk again in the morning.

237
00:35:36,176 --> 00:35:39,179
听我一句，行者，你别无选择
Word of advice, Walker. It's not a choice.

238
00:35:41,514 --> 00:35:43,475
总会有选择
It's always a choice.

239
00:35:47,395 --> 00:35:50,649
有人会整晚待在你房外
There'll be someone outside your room all night

240
00:35:50,732 --> 00:35:52,400
如果你需要什么
if you need anything.

241
00:35:52,484 --> 00:35:54,069
我不需要任何东西
I don't need anything.

242
00:35:54,736 --> 00:35:56,279
说不准
You never know.

243
00:36:47,580 --> 00:36:51,876
这是给你的，是洗漱的水和一些吃的
This is for you. It's some water for washing and some food.

244
00:36:52,460 --> 00:36:55,880
还有点特别的藏品，是这里主人的敬意
Little special reserve, too,compliments of the house.

245
00:37:00,510 --> 00:37:04,013
我需要你接着这个或说点什么
这样我才能找到你
I need you to take this or say something so I can find you.

246
00:37:15,900 --> 00:37:19,362
- 谢谢- 不客气
- Thank you.- You're welcome.

247
00:37:19,446 --> 00:37:22,240
- 你还需要点什么吗？- 不，我很好，谢谢
- Can I get you anything else?- No, I'm fine. Thank you.

248
00:37:22,449 --> 00:37:25,326
你是在战争中失明的，还是因为之后的太阳？
Did you get blinded in the war or by the sun after?

249
00:37:27,996 --> 00:37:30,582
我生来就这样
I was born this way.

250
00:37:30,665 --> 00:37:33,543
我想可能是我幸运，因为在它发生的时候
I think probably I'm lucky, because I was already used to being like this

251
00:37:33,626 --> 00:37:35,670
我就已经习惯这样了
by the time it happened.

252
00:37:36,337 --> 00:37:38,923
是的，谢谢你的食物
Right, well, thank you for the food.

253
00:37:39,549 --> 00:37:41,050
不客气
You're welcome.

254
00:37:43,303 --> 00:37:45,013
我喜欢你的香水
I like your perfume.

255
00:37:49,726 --> 00:37:51,436
不过是洗发水
It's just shampoo,

256
00:37:52,562 --> 00:37:54,189
但是谢谢
but thank you.

257
00:37:56,816 --> 00:37:58,193
晚安
Good night.

258
00:38:22,133 --> 00:38:25,637
我认为他早上是不会改主意的
I don't think he's gonna change his mind by the morning.

259
00:38:26,638 --> 00:38:28,515
他不会留下的
He's not gonna stay.

260
00:38:32,936 --> 00:38:35,063
他跟别人不同
He's different than the others.

261
00:38:36,064 --> 00:38:40,109
你不能像使唤别人那样，使唤他
You're not gonna be able to make him do what you want him to do.

262
00:38:41,945 --> 00:38:44,113
谁说我要出马？
Who said anything about me?

263
00:38:46,491 --> 00:38:48,493
我会派索拉娜去
I'll send Solara.

264
00:38:52,539 --> 00:38:54,499
你不能这么做
You can't do that.

265
00:38:54,582 --> 00:38:57,710
是更好地利用她的时候了
It's about time I got better use out of her.

266
00:39:00,046 --> 00:39:01,172
不要
Don't.

267
00:39:02,173 --> 00:39:03,424
拜托
Please.

268
00:39:04,425 --> 00:39:08,596
求求你，不要，求求你
Please, don't. Please. Please.

269
00:39:10,640 --> 00:39:11,933
求求你！
Please!

270
00:39:23,861 --> 00:39:25,530
我能进来吗？
Can I come in?

271
00:39:28,074 --> 00:39:29,742
等一下
Give me a minute.

272
00:39:38,710 --> 00:39:41,671
已经有人拿来吃的和水
Somebody already came with food and water.

273
00:39:44,090 --> 00:39:46,134
我需要的都有了
I got everything I need.

274
00:39:50,388 --> 00:39:52,473
你确定吗？
Are you sure about that?

275
00:39:56,102 --> 00:39:58,396
这里真的很亮
It's really bright in here.

276
00:40:00,064 --> 00:40:01,232
我是索拉娜
I'm Solara.

277
00:40:01,316 --> 00:40:05,069
是的，你刚在楼下装满了我的水壶
Right. You filled my canteen downstairs.

278
00:40:06,112 --> 00:40:08,990
是的，你是那个行者，对吗？
Yeah. You're the walker, right?

279
00:40:10,033 --> 00:40:11,242
是
Right.

280
00:40:14,454 --> 00:40:18,374
别担心钱，是记在这酒吧的账上的
If you're worried about paying, it's on the house.

281
00:40:18,458 --> 00:40:20,084
付什么钱？
Paying for what?

282
00:40:22,170 --> 00:40:24,172
你为什么不坐下来？
Why don't you take a seat?

283
00:40:34,140 --> 00:40:35,266
不
No.

284
00:40:37,268 --> 00:40:41,189
不，我不能走，我不能，如果我走了，他会伤害我妈妈
No, I can't go. I can't. If I do, he'll hurt my mom.

285
00:40:42,273 --> 00:40:44,192
- 谁？- 卡内基
- Who?- Carnegie.

286
00:40:46,319 --> 00:40:47,403
他是你爸爸？
He's your father?

287
00:40:48,196 --> 00:40:51,199
不，但我们都是属于他的
No. No, but we belong to him just the same.

288
00:40:51,282 --> 00:40:54,535
我会睡在地板上
Look, I'll sleep on the floor.

289
00:40:54,702 --> 00:40:56,245
明天告诉他，你过得很愉快
Tomorrow you can tell him you had a good time.

290
00:40:56,329 --> 00:40:59,082
我向你保证我不会惹麻烦的
I promise you I will be no trouble.

291
00:41:02,919 --> 00:41:04,212
求求你？
Please?

292
00:41:11,052 --> 00:41:14,764
马走到象四
Knight to bishop four.

293
00:41:22,814 --> 00:41:24,315
该你了
Your move.

294
00:41:31,239 --> 00:41:33,950
你多大？
So, how old are you?

295
00:41:34,909 --> 00:41:36,327
什么？
Excuse me?

296
00:41:36,411 --> 00:41:41,249
我只是以前没见过多少
你这个年龄的人路过这里
It's just that I haven't really seen too many people your age come through here before.

297
00:41:41,332 --> 00:41:43,543
自末日
Well, it's been

298
00:41:47,797 --> 00:41:50,216
已经有30个冬天了
30 winters since the flash.

299
00:41:53,678 --> 00:41:55,304
我真的记不清了
I really don't remember.

300
00:41:56,597 --> 00:42:00,852
你记得那时什么样吗？我是说以前的世界
Do you remember what it was like?I mean, in the world before.

301
00:42:00,935 --> 00:42:02,186
是的
Yeah.

302
00:42:05,857 --> 00:42:07,775
那是什么样子？
Well, what was it like?

303
00:42:11,946 --> 00:42:14,323
人们除了必需的，还拥有很多
People had more than they needed.

304
00:42:16,284 --> 00:42:20,621
我们不知道哪些是珍贵的，哪些不是
We had no idea what was precious, what wasn't.

305
00:42:25,626 --> 00:42:29,338
我们扔掉的那些东西现在人们却要争得你死我活
We threw away things people kill each other for now.

306
00:42:31,632 --> 00:42:33,468
- 真的？- 是的
- Really?- Yeah.

307
00:42:35,636 --> 00:42:37,096
你有本书
You have a book.

308
00:42:37,180 --> 00:42:39,307
- 我可以看一下吗？- 不，不可以
- Can I see it?- No, you cannot.

309
00:42:39,390 --> 00:42:41,601
- 我只是想看看- 不，我说过不行
- I just, I just wanna look at it.- No. I said no.

310
00:42:41,684 --> 00:42:44,312
听着，我甚至不识字！拜托，让我看看
Listen, I can't even read! Come on, please, let me just see it.

311
00:42:46,397 --> 00:42:48,065
你至于吗？只是本书！
What is with you? It is just a book!

312
00:42:48,149 --> 00:42:49,901
这不仅仅是一本书
It's not just a book.

313
00:42:50,568 --> 00:42:53,070
- 什么意思，这不只是一本书？- 听着
- What do you mean, it's not just a book?- Look.

314
00:42:53,154 --> 00:42:57,658
不要再问有关书的问题了，好吗？不要再问问题，好吧？
No more questions about the book, all right? No more questions. All right?

315
00:43:22,725 --> 00:43:25,103
既然你在这儿，我有个问题问你
I got a question for you, since you're here.

316
00:43:25,603 --> 00:43:27,939
我或许会回答，或许不
Well, maybe I'll answer it and maybe I won't.

317
00:43:30,024 --> 00:43:31,734
你从哪里弄到水？
Where do you get your water?

318
00:43:32,693 --> 00:43:34,070
不能告诉你
Can't tell you that.

319
00:43:34,153 --> 00:43:37,281
- 你不能告诉我还是你不知道？- 我知道
- You can't tell me or you don't know?- Oh, I know.

320
00:43:38,032 --> 00:43:43,162
但是如果你不告诉我这本书，我就不告诉你水的事
But if you're not talking about the book, I'm not talking about the water.

321
00:43:46,791 --> 00:43:48,835
你真有办法
You're something else, you know.

322
00:43:49,710 --> 00:43:51,629
好吧，我问你另外一个问题
All right, I got another question for you.

323
00:43:51,712 --> 00:43:53,339
好
Right.

324
00:43:53,422 --> 00:43:55,633
你饿吗？
You hungry?

325
00:43:55,716 --> 00:43:57,718
这儿有很多吃的
There's a lot of food there,

326
00:43:58,094 --> 00:43:59,846
我吃不了
more than I can eat.

327
00:44:00,930 --> 00:44:02,390
告诉你
Tell you what.

328
00:44:02,473 --> 00:44:06,894
我们可以一起分享，就像过去老人那样
We can share it, you know,like old people used to.

329
00:44:09,272 --> 00:44:11,023
好
Okay.

330
00:44:11,107 --> 00:44:12,233
好吗？
Okay?

331
00:44:16,863 --> 00:44:19,574
等等，等下，坐下
Wait a minute, wait a minute. Wait. Sit.

332
00:44:21,909 --> 00:44:22,994
坐下
Sit.

333
00:44:24,787 --> 00:44:26,914
这是给你的
This'll be for you.

334
00:44:27,790 --> 00:44:29,083
把手给我
Give me your hands.

335
00:44:31,252 --> 00:44:32,587
你在做什么？
What are you doing?

336
00:44:32,920 --> 00:44:34,922
相信我，把手给我
Trust me. Give me your hands.

337
00:44:39,302 --> 00:44:40,928
闭上你的眼睛
Close your eyes.

338
00:44:42,930 --> 00:44:45,850
亲爱的主，感谢你赐给我们食物
Dear Lord, we thank you for this meal.

339
00:44:45,933 --> 00:44:49,395
感谢你赐给我们温暖的床
We thank you for a warm bed

340
00:44:49,478 --> 00:44:53,357
以及在寒冷的夜晚，我们头顶的这项屋檐
and a roof over our head on cold nights such as this.

341
00:44:54,275 --> 00:44:56,152
这些已经久违了
It's been too long.

342
00:44:56,485 --> 00:44:58,070
这是从你书里来的吗？
Is this from your book?

343
00:44:59,113 --> 00:45:01,782
别打乱，闭上你的眼睛
Don't interrupt. Close your eyes.

344
00:45:03,701 --> 00:45:08,039
我们感谢你在这样艰难的时间里
We thank you for the gift of companionship

345
00:45:08,122 --> 00:45:10,458
赐给我们友谊
in hard times like these.

346
00:45:11,334 --> 00:45:12,710
阿门
Amen.

347
00:45:17,381 --> 00:45:18,841
现在可以吃了吗？
Now we eat?

348
00:45:20,092 --> 00:45:21,636
可以了
Now we eat.

349
00:45:52,667 --> 00:45:54,168
早上好，索拉娜
Good morning, Solara.

350
00:45:55,878 --> 00:45:58,673
昨晚如何？你睡得好吗？
How was your night? Did you sleep well?

351
00:45:58,756 --> 00:46:00,424
我按你说的做了
I did like you said.

352
00:46:00,675 --> 00:46:02,927
你当然会按照我说的去做
Of course you did what I said.

353
00:46:04,011 --> 00:46:07,348
但是有用吗？他会留下吗？
But did it work? Is he staying?

354
00:46:08,265 --> 00:46:10,351
我们没聊太多
We didn't do much talking.

355
00:46:11,268 --> 00:46:13,521
索拉娜，亲爱的，吃点东西
Solara, honey, eat something.

356
00:46:17,108 --> 00:46:19,026
妈，把你的手给我
Mom, give me your hand.

357
00:46:21,696 --> 00:46:23,364
闭上你的眼睛
Close your eyes.

358
00:46:23,990 --> 00:46:25,533
妈，相信我
Mom, trust me.

359
00:46:32,206 --> 00:46:33,457
亲爱的主
Dear Lord.

360
00:46:35,376 --> 00:46:37,461
我们感谢你赐予的食物
We thank you for our food.

361
00:46:38,796 --> 00:46:40,756
感谢你赐给我母亲
Thank you for my mother.

362
00:46:42,550 --> 00:46:46,429
感谢你赐给我们屋顶，以及我们的新朋友
Thank you for the roof over our heads and our new friends.

363
00:46:49,223 --> 00:46:50,474
还有…
And...

364
00:46:56,230 --> 00:46:58,899
我想目前就这么多
Well, I guess that's all for now.

365
00:46:59,567 --> 00:47:00,901
阿门
Amen.

366
00:47:06,949 --> 00:47:09,785
这是你要记住的词，阿门
That's the word you're looking for. Amen.

367
00:47:12,204 --> 00:47:13,956
这是结尾
That's how you stop.

368
00:47:20,921 --> 00:47:23,174
你说你们没聊什么
You said you didn't talk much.

369
00:47:25,259 --> 00:47:27,470
那他读了什么没有？
But did he do any reading?

370
00:47:29,764 --> 00:47:32,433
- 我在问你问题- 比尔，别
- I asked you a question.- Bill, don't.

371
00:47:32,516 --> 00:47:35,102
你，闭上你的嘴
You. Shut your mouth.

372
00:47:45,863 --> 00:47:47,031
住手！
Stop!

373
00:47:47,948 --> 00:47:49,784
你在伤害你的母亲，索拉娜
You're hurting your mother, Solara.

374
00:47:50,618 --> 00:47:53,913
他说过他每天都阅读的，是吗？
He said he read every day. Did he?

375
00:47:54,955 --> 00:47:56,374
住手！
Stop it!

376
00:47:57,291 --> 00:47:59,377
你妈妈希望你告诉我
Your mother would like you to tell me.

377
00:47:59,460 --> 00:48:00,961
我不知道！
I don't know!

